MAGNETIC
DISTURBANCES
AND
THE
EARTHS
MAGNETIC
FIELD
STORM
TIME
CHANGES
IN
THE
EARTHS
MAGNETIC
FIELD
COULD
INDUCE
CURRENTS
IN
THE
EARTHS
CORE
WHICH
INTERACT
WITH
THE
STEADY
FIELD
THIS
PRODUCES
A
NETT
UNIDIRECTIONAL
CURRENT
AT
THE
